        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 3:59PM PDT until July 1 at 5:00PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>SVRMFR

The National Weather Service in Medford has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Douglas County in southwestern Oregon...
Northeastern Jackson County in southwestern Oregon...
West central Klamath County in south central Oregon...

* Until 500 PM PDT.

* At 358 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Thousand
Springs Sno-Park, or 8 miles west of Crater Lake, moving northwest
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Crater Lake, Crater Lake National Park, Crater Lake Lodge, Highway
138 Diamond Lake Summit, Union Creek, Diamond Lake, Thousand
Springs Sno-Park, Broken Arrow Campground, Highway 62 Near Crater
Lake, Thielsen View Campground, Rogue Gorge, and Natural Bridge
Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
